{"NOL-PROS":[{"def":"To discontinue by entering a nolle prosequi; to decline to prosecute.","pos":""}],"NOLI-ME-TANGERE":[{"def":"A name formerly applied to several varieties of ulcerous cutaneous diseases, but now restricted to Lupus exedens, an ulcerative affection of the nose.","pos":""}],"NOLITION":[{"def":"Adverse action of will; unwillingness; -- opposed to Ant: volition.","pos":""}],"NOLL":[{"def":"The head; the noddle.","pos":""}],"NOLLE PROSEQUI":[{"def":"Will not prosecute; -- an entry on the record, denoting that a plaintiff discontinues his suit, or the attorney for the public a prosecution; either wholly, or as to some count, or as to some of several defendants.","pos":""}],"NOLLEITY":[{"def":"The state of being unwilling; nolition.","pos":""}],"NOLO CONTENDERE":[{"def":"A plea, by the defendant, in a criminal prosecution, which, without admitting guilt, subjects him to all the consequences of a plea of quilty.","pos":""}]}